{
  "texts": [
    "I am humbled and grateful for the contributions of everyone mentioned here and many others who have influenced this work.",
    "The essence of real-time systems lies in their ability to adhere to strict timing constraints, where the timeliness of task execution is essential.",
    "This characteristic distinguishes real-time systems from traditional computing systems, where performance is often measured by throughput or computational power alone.",
    "In real-time applications, failing to execute a task within the specified time frame can lead to unacceptable outcomes, ranging from system malfunction to catastrophic events, underscoring the profound implications of timing on system reliability and safety.",
    "Therefore, real-time systems are carefully designed to ensure that tasks are executed within precise deadlines, guaranteeing that critical operations are performed in a timely manner."
  ]
}